{
  "schema_version": "lmctl/v3",
  "definition_schema_version": 3,
  "name": "bugfix-pr-fixer-autosubmit-v2",
  "version": 1,
  "description": "Claims a bugfix task, repairs it with review, and prepares an autosubmitted pull request when the fix is ready.",
  "estimated_duration_ms": 360000,
  "default_task_timeout_ms": 1800000,
  "steps": [
    {
      "id": "s-reproduce-c7e8",
      "name": "reproduce",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "writes_to_project_path": true,
        "max_loops": 2
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "prompt_template": "Work in {{project.local_path}}. If that directory does not contain a checkout of {{project.owner}}/{{project.repo}}, `git clone https://github.com/{{project.owner}}/{{project.repo}}.git {{project.local_path}}` first. Then `cd {{project.local_path}}` before any further commands. Do NOT operate inside your agent sessiondir.\n\nReproduce the bug reported in {{job_payload.issue_url}}:\n1. `gh issue view {{job_payload.issue_url}}` to read the body.\n2. Install dependencies if needed (the project's test command is the focused_test step downstream — match it).\n3. Write the minimum repro from the issue body inside {{project.local_path}}.\n4. Run the project's test command against the bug's area to confirm reproduction (the repro should fail before the fix).\n5. Save the repro snippet so the reviewer can verify.\n\nReturn STANCE: <reproduced|failed>"
        },
        "reviewers": [
          {
            "team": "default",
            "alias": "Reviewer1"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-root-cause-ebd0",
      "name": "root_cause",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "max_loops": 5
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "prompt_template": "`cd {{project.local_path}}` first; investigate inside the project checkout, not your sessiondir.\n\nYou just reproduced {{job_payload.issue_url}}. Find the root cause:\n1. Investigate the codebase via grep/cat/etc inside {{project.local_path}}.\n2. Identify the exact file + line + reason for the bug.\n3. Return STANCE: <found|hypothesized|none|failed>"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-fix-05d0",
      "name": "fix",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "writes_to_project_path": true,
        "max_loops": 5
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "prompt_template": "`cd {{project.local_path}}` first. All git operations must happen in the project checkout, NOT your sessiondir.\n\nApply the fix you root-caused for {{job_payload.issue_url}}:\n1. `cd {{project.local_path}}` and create a feature branch: `git checkout -b lmctl-next/run-{{run_id}}-issue-X` (replace X with the issue number).\n2. Edit the buggy file.\n3. Add a regression test in the project's test layout (tests/, *_test.go, etc.).\n4. Run the project's test command (matches the focused_test step downstream) to confirm all tests pass.\n5. `git add` + `git commit` on the branch with a concise subject like `Fix issue #X: <short summary>`.\n\nSTANCE: <applied|failed>"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-focused-test-2a4f",
      "name": "focused_test",
      "type": "lmctl/shell-step",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "command": "{{project.test_command}}",
        "outcomes_from_exit": {
          "0": "@terminal:exit_0",
          "default": "@terminal:exit_default"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-code-review-3974",
      "name": "code_review",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "writes_to_project_path": true,
        "max_loops": 3
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "prompt_template": "`cd {{project.local_path}}` first. Confirm the fix for {{job_payload.issue_url}} is committed on the feature branch and tests pass.\n\nRun `git log -1` to verify the commit exists and `git diff <repo-default-branch>..HEAD --stat` (the repo's actual default branch: usually `main` or `master`) to summarize. Verify HEAD is on the feature branch you created in the fix step.\n\nSTANCE: committed | failed"
        },
        "reviewers": [
          {
            "team": "default",
            "alias": "Reviewer1"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-internal-pr-artifact-a803",
      "name": "internal_pr_artifact",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "max_loops": 5
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "prompt_template": "Draft a PR body for the fix you applied to {{job_payload.issue_url}}.\n\nInclude: brief problem statement, root cause, the change, focused test summary. NO emoji, NO AI tells (claude/codex/gemini/anthropic/openai), NO 'Generated with' or 'Co-Authored-By' lines, NO 'as an AI' phrases. Plain professional prose.\n\nSave the body to /tmp/lmctl-next-run-{{run_id}}-pr-draft.md and reply with STANCE: built | failed"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-polish-1dc9",
      "name": "polish",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "max_loops": 5
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Polisher",
          "prompt_template": "Read /tmp/lmctl-next-run-{{run_id}}-pr-draft.md. Tighten it: remove redundant phrases, make it concise. Preserve all technical content. NO emoji, NO AI tells.\n\nOverwrite the file with the polished version. STANCE: rewrote | failed"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-scrub-042b",
      "name": "scrub",
      "type": "lmctl/shell-step",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "command": "perl /home/mma/bugfix/factory/pr_lint.pl /tmp/lmctl-next-pr-draft.md",
        "outcomes_from_exit": {
          "0": "@terminal:exit_0",
          "default": "@terminal:exit_default"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-finalize-4c46",
      "name": "finalize",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "writes_to_project_path": true,
        "max_loops": 5
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "prompt_template": "Move the polished PR body from /tmp/lmctl-next-run-{{run_id}}-pr-draft.md to {{project.local_path}}/PR_BODY.md.\n\n1. cat /tmp/lmctl-next-run-{{run_id}}-pr-draft.md\n2. cp /tmp/lmctl-next-run-{{run_id}}-pr-draft.md {{project.local_path}}/PR_BODY.md\n3. Print the file path + size to confirm.\n\nSTANCE: finalized | failed"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-submit-pr-gate-0fd1",
      "name": "submit_pr_gate",
      "type": "lmctl/interactive",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "termination": {
          "operator_signal": true,
          "max_turns": 1
        }
      },
      "members": {
        "agent": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "initial_prompt_template": "Ready to push the feature branch and open a PR for {{job_payload.issue_url}}. Review the artifacts and signal done to proceed with the push and PR creation."
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-submit-pr-944d",
      "name": "submit_pr",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "writes_to_project_path": true,
        "max_loops": 5
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "prompt_template": "`cd {{project.local_path}}` first. Push the feature branch to origin and open the PR.\n\n1. Determine the branch name from HEAD: `git rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD`.\n2. Push: `git push -u origin <branch>`. If push fails, STANCE: push_failed.\n3. Open the PR via gh:\n   gh pr create --repo {{project.owner}}/{{project.repo}} --base main --head <branch> --title \"<PR title — same as the commit subject, e.g. 'Fix issue #X: <short summary>'>\" --body-file {{project.local_path}}/PR_BODY.md\n4. Capture the PR URL gh prints to stdout and write it to /tmp/lmctl-next-run-{{run_id}}-pr-url.txt.\n5. STANCE: submitted on success; create_failed if gh pr create fails."
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-merge-pr-gate-3a7d",
      "name": "merge_pr_gate",
      "type": "lmctl/interactive",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "termination": {
          "operator_signal": true,
          "max_turns": 1
        }
      },
      "members": {
        "agent": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "initial_prompt_template": "PR has been opened for {{job_payload.issue_url}}. Ready to merge. Signal done to proceed with the merge."
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-merge-pr-e7a5",
      "name": "merge_pr",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "max_loops": 5
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "prompt_template": "Read the PR URL from /tmp/lmctl-next-run-{{run_id}}-pr-url.txt. Merge it.\n\n1. PR_URL=$(cat /tmp/lmctl-next-run-{{run_id}}-pr-url.txt)\n2. gh pr merge \"$PR_URL\" --repo {{project.owner}}/{{project.repo}} --merge --delete-branch\n3. Verify state via `gh pr view \"$PR_URL\" --json state,mergedAt,mergeCommit`. Expected: state=MERGED.\n\nSTANCE:\n- `merged`: PR is MERGED and the head branch was deleted.\n- `merge_blocked`: gh pr merge exited non-zero with output indicating a protection rule, CI failure, or unmet status check (operator should review before retrying).\n- `failed`: gh call errored for other reasons (auth, network, etc.)."
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-human-escalate-gate-a009",
      "name": "human_escalate_gate",
      "type": "lmctl/interactive",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "termination": {
          "operator_signal": true,
          "max_turns": 1
        }
      },
      "members": {
        "agent": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "initial_prompt_template": "Auto-submit workflow paused for {{job_payload.issue_url}}. One of the upstream steps reported failure or uncertain. Check the run's step list for the last non-success outcome and review the artifacts under /tmp/lmctl-next-run-{{run_id}}-*. Choose: approve (operator resolved manually), reject (abandon), or retry_merge (retry just the merge_pr step, e.g. after CI cleared). Signal done when ready."
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-human-escalate-decide-500d",
      "name": "human_escalate_decide",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "max_loops": 5
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "prompt_template": "The operator has reviewed the situation for {{job_payload.issue_url}}. Based on the conversation context, determine their decision.\n\nIf the operator approved (resolved manually): STANCE: approved\nIf the operator rejected (abandon): STANCE: rejected\nIf the operator wants to retry the merge: STANCE: retry_merge"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-terminal-aborted-ffda",
      "name": "terminal:aborted",
      "type": "lmctl/terminal",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "name": "aborted",
        "kind": "failure"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-terminal-pr-merged-265a",
      "name": "terminal:pr_merged",
      "type": "lmctl/terminal",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "name": "pr_merged",
        "kind": "success"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-terminal-pr-ready-d1c6",
      "name": "terminal:pr_ready",
      "type": "lmctl/terminal",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "name": "pr_ready",
        "kind": "success"
      }
    }
  ],
